article.headline: Toledo 78, Central Michigan 62
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- A layup by Florentino Valencia gave Toledo a double-digit lead less than five minutes into the second half, and the Rockets led by at least 10 the rest of the way en route to a 78-62 victory over Central Michigan on Saturday night. Valencia was 9-of-10 from the field and finished with 23 points for Toledo (11-9, 4-8 Mid-American Conference). Keonta Howell added 19. Sefton Barrett led Central Michigan (3-17, 1-11) with 17 points and 12 rebounds. Justin Blevins had 14 points, and Giordan Watson had 12. Valencia hit a jumper inside the first half minute of play and Toledo never trailed in the game, although the Chippewas tied once at 26 on a pair of free throws by Chris Kellerman. Toledo then put together an 11-1 run, and Central Michigan went the final seven minutes of the half without a field goal.
